# <%= projectName %>

## Prerequisites

- Nix for the generated language-specific development shell

## Setup

```bash
nix develop path:.
go mod tidy
pre-commit install
make check
```

The generated `flake.nix` provides Go <%= toolchain.go %>+ plus `golangci-lint`,
`staticcheck`, `deadcode`, `govulncheck`, `goimports`, `go-mutesting`,
`gitleaks`, and `pre-commit`.

## Development

| Command | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `make lint` | Run golangci-lint and custom anvil analyzers |
| `make format` | Check Go formatting |
| `make typecheck` | Run go vet and staticcheck |
| `make security` | Scan for secrets |
| `make test` | Run Go tests |
| `make coverage` | Run tests with coverage thresholds |
| `make deadcode` | Detect unused code |
| `make crap` | Compute CRAP scores |
| `make audit` | Run govulncheck |
| `make mutate` | Run Go mutation testing |
| `make check` | Run tier 1 and tier 2 validation |
| `make quality` | Run all validation, including mutation testing |
| `make fix` | Auto-format Go source files |

## Anvil-generated validation gates

Anvil wires validation through the generated `Makefile`. Run `make check`
before handoff or push. Run `make quality` at the final quality boundary when
you need the mutation gate too.

`AGENTS.md` gives coding agents repo-local instructions. `.anvil.lock` records
the Anvil version, toolchain versions, generated files, and checksums used for
safe re-scaffold decisions. Do not edit `.anvil.lock` by hand; rerun `anvil
init` or `anvil doctor` instead.

The seed/reference code demonstrates conventions to follow: package structure,
tests, typed errors, constants, enums, and structured logging.

## Project Structure

```text
cmd/app/         Application entrypoint
internal/seed/   Reference package and tests
tools/go-analyzers/ Custom analyzers and CRAP reporting
```
